# Purpose

Query HCUP NIS 2023 (National Inpatient Sample) for ICD-10-PCS facial nerve
codes beyond the Repair (01QM) family, to determine whether inpatient facial
nerve reconstruction is captured under Supplement (01UM) or Reposition (01SM)
codes. Prior 01QM query returned 3 unweighted (15 weighted) cases — this run
determines whether the inpatient arm of the parallel NASS/NIS study is viable
or should be reframed as a brief descriptive comparator.

**Source file:** `NIS_2023_Core.ASC` — fixed-width ASCII, 643 bytes per record.
Column positions derived from `StataLoad_NIS_2023_Core.Do` (HCUP, 12/10/2025).
Only the columns needed for this query are read; all others are skipped,
keeping memory well below the 4.34 GB file size.

**Codes queried:**

- `01QM0ZZ / 01QM3ZZ / 01QM4ZZ` — Repair Facial Nerve, PNS (QC vs. prior run)
- `01UM07Z / 01UM0KZ / 01UM0JZ` — Supplement Facial Nerve, Open
- `01SM0ZZ` — Reposition Facial Nerve, Open
- `00QM0ZZ / 00QM3ZZ / 00QM4ZZ` — CNS-section codes (negative control, expect 0)

